dspSapTable.name: dspSapTable
dspSapTable.description: A table containing configuration information about all the service access point.

dspSapEntry.name: dspSapEntry
dspSapEntry.description: The parameters for a particular service access point.

dspSapNumber.name: dspSapNumber
dspSapNumber.description: Identifies the service access point by a numerical value. This value is used as a index in the saps table. Values are unique per service access point.

dspSapRowStatus.name: dspSapRowStatus
dspSapRowStatus.description: Indicates whether the particular service access point is configured within the MIB Service access point entries (rows) may be created by setting this object value to 'valid', or deleted by changing this object value to 'invalid'. Whether or not the row actually disappears is left to the implementation so this object may actually read as 'invalid' for some arbitrary length of time.

dspSapType.name: dspSapType
dspSapType.description: Identifies the service access point by type:'lower' identifies a SAP leading to a physical X25 port. 'Upper' identifies a SAP acting as an internal inter-layer logical port.

dspSapAlias.name: dspSapAlias
dspSapAlias.description: Identifies the service access point by a textual name. Names are unique per service access point.

dspSapCompanionAlias.name: dspSapCompanionAlias
dspSapCompanionAlias.description: Identifies the `lower' service access point that will communicate with this service access point by a textual name. Names are unique per service access point. Used to bind the DSP Sap with the X25 sap.

dspSapSnalcRef.name: dspSapSnalcRef
dspSapSnalcRef.description: Identifies which upper sap is associated to the lower sap within the DSP module. Applies only to lower DSP saps (X25 sap).

dspSapEbcdicAsciiMode.name: dspSapEbcdicAsciiMode
dspSapEbcdicAsciiMode.description: Indicates the character set used by the device defined for this association. The character set could be a EBCDIC or ASCII.

dspSapControl.name: dspSapControl
dspSapControl.description: Control associated with the specified service access point.

dspSapOperationalMode.name: dspSapOperationalMode
dspSapOperationalMode.description: Identifies the service access point as being active or non-active with the new configuration.

dspCuTable.name: dspCuTable
dspCuTable.description: A table containing configuration information about all the 3270 controller units.

dspCuEntry.name: dspCuEntry
dspCuEntry.description: The parameters for a particular controller unit.

dspCuSapNumber.name: dspCuSapNumber
dspCuSapNumber.description: Identifies the sap associated with this controller unit. Each controller unit has an address and the address has to be unique with one sap. However, the address is not required to be unique between saps This object is an index in the sap Table. Values are unique.

dspCuAddress.name: dspCuAddress
dspCuAddress.description: Identifies the address of this controller unit. The address has to be unique for a specified sap.

dspCuRowStatus.name: dspCuRowStatus
dspCuRowStatus.description: Indicates whether the particular service access point is configured within the MIB. Controller unit entries (rows) may be created by setting this object value to 'valid', or deleted by changing this object value to 'invalid'. Whether or not the row actually disappears is left to the implementation so this object may actually read as 'invalid' for some arbitrary length of time.

dspCuType.name: dspCuType
dspCuType.description: Identifies the type of controller: either TIU or HIU.

dspCuCallingX25Address.name: dspCuCallingX25Address
dspCuCallingX25Address.description: Identifies the X25 address of this sap. This address is unique for all devices attached to this sap, TIU side

dspCuCalledX25Address.name: dspCuCalledX25Address
dspCuCalledX25Address.description: Identifies the X25 address of the remote device.

dspCuDSPCircuitType.name: dspCuDSPCircuitType
dspCuDSPCircuitType.description: Identifies the connection as being either only one connection or multiple DSP connections per X.25 virtual circuit The valid values follow: singUsr-NoReq Circ - single user per X25 svc, no circuit request. The LCN is 0. singUsr-ReqCirc - single user per X25 svc, circuit request. The LCN is negociated during the connection establishment. multUser-ReqCirc - multiple user per X25 svc. Each user has a LCN and the LCN is negociated individually. MES-Usr-ReqCirc - Modified Bisync single user per X25 svc, circuit request. The LCN is negociated during the connection establishment.

dspCuWindow.name: dspCuWindow
dspCuWindow.description: Defines the receive window size used for packets. At the source side, it defines the window for packets received from the source interface. At the destination side, it defines the window for packets transmitted to the the source side, it defines the window for packets transmitted to the source interface. At the destination side, it defines the window for packets received from the destination interface. Allowable value are '1'-'7' for modulo 8.

dspCuUserData.name: dspCuUserData
dspCuUserData.description: The user data put in the call user data field of call request packets.

dspCuFacility.name: dspCuFacility
dspCuFacility.description: Specifies the facility codes and facility parameters put in the facilities field of the call call request packet during call set-up. The maximum number of facility codes and parameters that may be specified is 20.

dspCuApplicationId.name: dspCuApplicationId
dspCuApplicationId.description: Indicates an application running on the host associated with the controller unit/device.

dspCuReqMode.name: dspCuReqMode
dspCuReqMode.description: Identifies the connection request mode. The following modes are available : Fixed Class Crm : destination is selected automatically Specific Class Crm : select a destination by cu/dev addresses. Non-Specific Class Crm : select a destination by address and application ID. Associated Device Crm : associate a device with an existing connection. The terminal DSP uese the Only the 'fixedClassCrm' could be supported by this implementation.

dspCuPacketSize.name: dspCuPacketSize
dspCuPacketSize.description: The receive and transmit packet size.

dspCuThroughput.name: dspCuThroughput
dspCuThroughput.description: The receive and transmit throughput class across the line.

dspCuPartner.name: dspCuPartner
dspCuPartner.description: This object identifies the knowledge DSP has about its BSC partner layer and applies to the controllers acting as Terminal Interface. In normal conditions, the DSP and BSC layers are configured both having the same interface type (HIU or TIU). This is the default configuration and it enables the controller the be the initiator of the X25 connection. The host can't establish an X25 connection in this configuration. When the Host is the call establishment initiator, this object could be configured as Host (HIU) type and the local BSC as (TIU), meaning that the DSP will behave as a HIU during the call establishment. This object is used just during the call establishment. There are the following options available: terminal-terminal DSP and BSC layers are configured as hosts. host-terminal DSP is configured as host and behaves as a terminal. BSC is configured as a terminal.

dspCuControl.name: dspCuControl
dspCuControl.description: Control associated with the specified service access point.

dspCuState.name: dspCuState
dspCuState.description: Control associated with the specified service access point.

dspCuOperationalMode.name: dspCuOperationalMode
dspCuOperationalMode.description: Identifies the controller unit as being active or non-active with the new configuration.

dspCuX25CallRequest.name: dspCuX25CallRequest
dspCuX25CallRequest.description: Identifies the number of X25 Call Request packets received by this controller.

dspCuX25CallAccept.name: dspCuX25CallAccept
dspCuX25CallAccept.description: Identifies the number of X25 Call Accept packets received by this controller.

dspCuClears.name: dspCuClears
dspCuClears.description: Identifies the number of Clear Request received from the SNALC layer.

dspCuClearsInd.name: dspCuClearsInd
dspCuClearsInd.description: Identifies the number of Clear Indications sent to the SNALC layer.

dspCuInvToClear.name: dspCuInvToClear
dspCuInvToClear.description: Identifies the number of INVITATION TO CLEAR packets received by this controller.

dspDevTable.name: dspDevTable
dspDevTable.description: A table containing configuration information about all the devices controlled by this module.

dspDevEntry.name: dspDevEntry
dspDevEntry.description: The parameters for a particular controller unit.

dspDevSapNumber.name: dspDevSapNumber
dspDevSapNumber.description: Identifies the sap to which this device is attached to.

dspDevCuAddress.name: dspDevCuAddress
dspDevCuAddress.description: Identifies the address of the controller unit to which this device is attached.

dspDevAddress.name: dspDevAddress
dspDevAddress.description: Identifies the address of this device. The address has to be unique for a specified for a controller unit.

dspDevRowStatus.name: dspDevRowStatus
dspDevRowStatus.description: Indicates whether the particular service access point is configured within the MIB. Controller unit entries (rows) may be created by setting this object value to 'valid', or deleted by changing this object value to 'invalid'. Whether or not the row actually disappears is left to the implementation so this object may actually read as 'invalid' for some arbitrary length of time.

dspDevRemoteCuAddress.name: dspDevRemoteCuAddress
dspDevRemoteCuAddress.description: Identifies the address of remote controller unit to which this device is connected. This object is set to 0 if no connection is established.

dspDevRemoteDevAddress.name: dspDevRemoteDevAddress
dspDevRemoteDevAddress.description: Identifies the address of remote controller unit to which this device is connected. This object is set to 0 if no connection is established.

dspDevFormatSize.name: dspDevFormatSize
dspDevFormatSize.description: Describes the number of characters suported by the device.

dspDevAttPrnt.name: dspDevAttPrnt
dspDevAttPrnt.description: Identifies wheather the device has a printer attached. The device could be a display in order to have a printer attached.

dspDevCharSet.name: dspDevCharSet
dspDevCharSet.description: Identifies the support of different character sets.

dspDevColour.name: dspDevColour
dspDevColour.description: Identifies wheather the device supports colours.

dspDevTTextSupport.name: dspDevTTextSupport
dspDevTTextSupport.description: Identifies whether it the device supports transparent text.

dspDevDPmode.name: dspDevDPmode
dspDevDPmode.description: Identifies wheather the device is a display or printer.

dspDevControl.name: dspDevControl
dspDevControl.description: Control associated with the specified service access point.

dspDevOperationalMode.name: dspDevOperationalMode
dspDevOperationalMode.description: Identifies the controller unit as being active or non-active with the new configuration.

dspDevState.name: dspDevState
dspDevState.description: Indicates the state of the conection. The state 'invalid' means there is no connection. The state 'conected' means the connection is established.

dspDevStatus.name: dspDevStatus
dspDevStatus.description: This object contains the 'Status' byte, defined by the BSC protocol for 3270 controller unit family. This object and the 'bscDevSense ' contain the result of the last operations performed on the device. The controller unit is responsable to set properly this byte.

dspDevSense.name: dspDevSense
dspDevSense.description: This object contains the 'Sense' byte, defined by the BSC protocol for 3270 controller unit family. This object and the 'bscDevSense ' contain the result of the last operations performed on the device. The controller unit is responsable to set properly this byte.

dspDevCommand.name: dspDevCommand
dspDevCommand.description: Identifies the number of COMAMND packets sent/received by the device. Only the host sends the COMMAND packets. The host DSP counts the number of packets sent. The terminal DSP counts the number of packets received.

dspDevResponse.name: dspDevResponse
dspDevResponse.description: Identifies the number of RESPONSE packets sent/received by the device. Only the termianl sends RESPONSE packets. The host DSP counts the number of packets received. The terminal DSP counts the number of packets sent.

dspDevCmdRspUndel.name: dspDevCmdRspUndel
dspDevCmdRspUndel.description: Identifies the number of COMAMND/RESPONSE UNDELIVERED packets. This object notifies how many packets were rejected by this device. The host DSP counts the number of COMMAND ABORTED packets received. The terminal DSP counts the number of RESPONSE ABORTED packets received.. The error code of the last received packet (COMMAND/REPONSE) is kept by the object 'dspDevCmdRspUndelReason'.

dspDevCmdRspUndelReason.name: dspDevCmdRspUndelReason
dspDevCmdRspUndelReason.description: This object keeps the error code of the last COMAMND/RESPONSE UNDELIVERED packet received. When conected to another Memotec device, only the 'wack' reason code could be received. All other error codes are managed locally by BSC.

dspDevCmdRspAbort.name: dspDevCmdRspAbort
dspDevCmdRspAbort.description: Identifies the number of COMAMND/RESPONSE ABORTED packets. This object notifies how many packets were aborted by this device. The host DSP counts the number of COMMAND ABORTED packets received. The terminal DSP counts the number of RESPONSE ABORTED packets received.. The error code of the last received packet (COMMAND/REPONSE) is kept by the object dspDevCmdRspAbortReason.

dspDevCmdRspAbortReason.name: dspDevCmdRspAbortReason
dspDevCmdRspAbortReason.description: This object keeps the error code of the last COMAMND/RESPONSE ABORTED packet received. When conected to another Memotec device, all the abort cases are managed locally by BSC.

dspDevStatStatus.name: dspDevStatStatus
dspDevStatStatus.description: Identifies the number of STATUS packets sent/received. Only the terminal sends this packet. The terminal DSP counts the number of packets sent. The host DSP counts the number of packets received.

dspDevAck.name: dspDevAck
dspDevAck.description: Identifies the number of ACK packets sent by the device. Both host and terminal DSPs can sent ACK packets.

dspDevInvToClear.name: dspDevInvToClear
dspDevInvToClear.description: Identifies the number of INVITATION TO CLEAR packets received by the device.

dspDevInvClearReason.name: dspDevInvClearReason
dspDevInvClearReason.description: This object keeps the error code of the last COMAMND/RESPONSE ABORTED packet received.

dspDevReset.name: dspDevReset
dspDevReset.description: Identifies the number of RESET packets received by the device.

dspDevResetReason.name: dspDevResetReason
dspDevResetReason.description: This object keeps the error code of the last RESET packet received..

dspDevCircuitEnabled.name: dspDevCircuitEnabled
dspDevCircuitEnabled.description: Identifies the number of CIRCUIT ENABLED packets received by the device.

dspDevCircuitRequest.name: dspDevCircuitRequest
dspDevCircuitRequest.description: Identifies the number of CIRCUIT REQUEST packets received by the device.

dspDevCircuitDisconnect.name: dspDevCircuitDisconnect
dspDevCircuitDisconnect.description: Identifies the number of DISCONNECT packets received by the device.
